Grilled Flank Steak with Cilantro Scallion Puree

Steak:
1/4 c olive oil
2 tbsp sherry vinegar
1 tbsp sugar
1/2 tbsp crushed red pepper flakes
1 tsp espelette pepper
2 garlic cloves, minced
1 1/2-2lb flank steak
kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste

Marinate the steak. Light a grill. In a small bowl, whisk together all the ingredients except for the meat, salt and pepper. Pour the marinade into a large sealable plastic bag with the meat. Seal and turn to fully coat. Marinate for 15 min.

Puree:
1 c cilantro leaves
1/2 c olive oil
2 tbsp lime juice
1/4 tsp worcestershire sauce
2 garlic cloves
2 scallions, roughly chopped
pinch ground cumin

In a blender, add all ingredients and blend until the souce comes together.


Remove the steak from the marinade and season with salt and pepper. Grill until medium rare, 6-7 min per side. Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 3-5 min, then thinly slice against the grain. Drizzle with puree and serve.
